Gauteng Education MEC Panyaza Lesufi is taking aim at Umalusi. He says the education quality assurance body has been unfair to the class of 2020. #eNCA​ Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Gauteng Education MEC Panyaza Lesufi says education quality assurance body Umalusi, has been unfair to the class of 2020. Umalusi reduced the marks in eight subjects in which pupils performed better than normal. READ: Matrics achieve 76.2% pass rate The province boasts the top five districts in the country and honoured its top achievers at an official ceremony on Wednesday. Watch the video above for more details on this story.